	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">never-obsolete wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">now the wiki says to blank the screen and only place white where the object is. now is this done with name tables or sprites, or does it not matter?</div>
<br />It doesn't matter, whatever is easier for you to code. The only thing the light gun does is detect the presence or absence of light.
<br />
<br />A good tip is to show a completely black screen before placing a white sprite at the place you are testing for a hit, and confirm that the gun detected black for that frame. If you don't, a player can just point the gun to a lightbulb and every shot will be considered a hit. So I heard.
<br />
<br />I think that the idea of a 2-player lightgun game is great!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


