	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">It's not true.</div><br />Not true for incandescent, tho I do have a flourescent light that will trigger the Zapper.  No idea how fast the light is supposed to be switching but it works fairly consistently.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> couldn't really come up with a good idea for that other than a fps</div>
<br />Doesn't Gotcha! (paintball game) use Zapper and controller?  It was like dpad to pan left/right and Zapper to shoot the people and items.
<br />
<br />For detection without scanline counting you might be able to do something like a binary search tree of the screen.  Start with half screen white, then each frame cut the amount of white in half.  Depending on the accuracy you want it should take ~4-6 frames.  Might be too much of a distraction or it might look really cool having the white area zoom to your target.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


