	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Cycle-timed Y position detection (white screen, timing from sprite 0 to the hit) allows the search to be narrowed down to plus or minus about 15 scanlines. Then a binary (as opposed to linear) search reduces the number of frames needed to narrow down which object was hit.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
